notes.title: Luke Skywalker
notes.content: A Jedi Knight who played a crucial role in defeating the Galactic Empire.

notes.title: Yoda
notes.content: A wise and powerful Jedi Master who trained many Jedi over centuries.

notes.title: Obi-Wan Kenobi
notes.content: A Jedi Master who trained Anakin Skywalker and later his son, Luke Skywalker.

notes.title: Anakin Skywalker
notes.content: A Jedi Knight who was prophesied to bring balance to the Force, but fell to the dark side.

notes.title: Mace Windu
notes.content: A senior member of the Jedi Council known for his skill in lightsaber combat.

notes.title: Qui-Gon Jinn
notes.content: A Jedi Master who discovered Anakin Skywalker and believed him to be the Chosen One.

notes.title: Ahsoka Tano
notes.content: Anakin Skywalker's Padawan who left the Jedi Order before the Clone Wars ended.

notes.title: Rey
notes.content: A scavenger from Jakku who became the last Jedi of the Skywalker saga.

notes.title: Kylo Ren
notes.content: Born Ben Solo, he was seduced to the dark side but was redeemed by Rey.

notes.title: Leia Organa
notes.content: A leader of the Rebel Alliance who later trained as a Jedi under her brother Luke.

notes.title: Jocasta Nu
notes.content: The Chief Librarian of the Jedi Archives.

notes.title: Plo Koon
notes.content: A Jedi Master who served as a General during the Clone Wars.

notes.title: Ki-Adi-Mundi
notes.content: A Cerean Jedi Master and member of the Jedi Council.

notes.title: Shaak Ti
notes.content: A Togruta Jedi Master and member of the Jedi Council.

notes.title: Kit Fisto
notes.content: A Nautolan Jedi Master known for his underwater combat skills.

notes.title: Luminara Unduli
notes.content: A Jedi Master who served as a General during the Clone Wars.

notes.title: Barriss Offee
notes.content: A Jedi Knight who turned against the Order during the Clone Wars.

notes.title: Aayla Secura
notes.content: A Twi'lek Jedi Master who served during the Clone Wars.

notes.title: Depa Billaba
notes.content: A Jedi Master and member of the Jedi Council.

notes.title: Adi Gallia
notes.content: A Tholothian Jedi Master and member of the Jedi Council.

notes.title: Eeth Koth
notes.content: A Zabrak Jedi Master and member of the Jedi Council.

notes.title: Saesee Tiin
notes.content: A Iktotchi Jedi Master known for his piloting skills.

notes.title: Oppo Rancisis
notes.content: A Thisspiasian Jedi Master and member of the Jedi Council.

notes.title: Even Piell
notes.content: A Lannik Jedi Master and member of the Jedi Council.

notes.title: Yaddle
notes.content: A Jedi Master of the same species as Yoda.

notes.title: Quinlan Vos
notes.content: A Jedi Master known for his unconventional methods.

notes.title: Jolee Bindo
notes.content: A Grey Jedi who fought in the Jedi Civil War.

notes.title: Nomi Sunrider
notes.content: A legendary Jedi Knight from the Old Republic era.

notes.title: Cade Skywalker
notes.content: A descendant of Luke Skywalker who struggled with his destiny.

notes.title: Kanan Jarrus
notes.content: A Jedi Knight who survived Order 66 and led the Ghost crew.
